tting ourselves in nature as we are. We are also changing who we are.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aEnvironmental policyxSocial aspects. 0aGreen movement. 0aPolitical ecology. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Studies. 4aLiterature : Literature. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Politics. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Environmental.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849427240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438494272423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438494272/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles